modules.description: This module extends X Windows graphics capabilities by enabling sub-window management alongside the main OCaml graphics window. It provides functions to generate unique window identifiers, create sub-windows at specified positions and dimensions, and close existing sub-windows using their identifiers. These operations are useful for building multi-pane visual interfaces or layered graphical applications directly within X11 environments.

This module enables low-level 2D rendering, window management, and event-driven input handling. It operates on geometric primitives (points, curves, polygons), color representations (RGB, predefined hues), and pixel buffers, supporting tasks like path-based drawing, text layout, and image manipulation. Typical applications include educational visualizations, simple game development, and interactive tools requiring precise graphical control and user interaction.
